      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(session): persist memory on auto daily/idle rollover",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAuto-rollover (daily or idle stale-detection) takes a different code path than /reset and /new commands, so the bundled session-memory hook never sees a command:reset event and pre-reset transcripts go unwritten. Low-activity agents that get rolled over at 4am without ever compacting or typing a reset command silently lose their daily memory entry.\r\n\r\nThis PR fires the same internal command:reset hook on stale rollover with a commandSource of 'auto:daily' or 'auto:idle' so existing listeners (including the bundled session-memory handler) persist memory for automatic reset paths too. Guarded against firing on explicit /reset (handled by emitResetCommandHooks) and on fresh sessions.\r\n\r\n## Change Type (select all)\r\n\r\n- [x] Bug fix\r\n- [ ] Feature\r\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\r\n- [x] Docs\r\n- [ ] Security hardening\r\n- [ ] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\r\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n- [x] Memory / storage\r\n- [ ] Integrations\r\n- [ ] API / contracts\r\n- [ ] UI / DX\r\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n- Related #8185, #37955\r\n- Closes #11960\r\n- [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n## Human verification\r\n\r\nVerified that the hook fires and creates the memory file on automatic reset.\r\n",
